Drop the entire ifdef block which allows compilation under Ruby 3.

commit.message:
Merge patch from Ben Smith for py3 compatibility

Merge patch from Ben Smith for py3 compatibility in the pylorcon2 lib;
highly recommended that tools use the python-cffi interface instead
because this library still has some issues.

Modernize float frequency to channel number instead of using lookup
table

Workaround for legacy Ruby 1.8 Global Interpreter Lock handling.
TRAP_BEG and TRAP_END are deprecated. Lorcon_capture_next() is likely broken.

* Fixed unclosed HAVE_LINUX_NETLINK.
